    "Furthermore, upper bounds for q 1 (G) (and for related expressions such as q 1 (G) + k, q 1 (G) k, q 1 (G).",
    "k, q 1 (G)/k) are determined for graphs G belonging to the set in n-1 k=1 T k n. In [24] the authors defined G n as the set of maximal outerplanar graphs with n vertices and no inner triangles (which are exactly the 2-path graphs).",
    "Then they proved that, the fixed order n graphs in G n with q 1 (G) (largest eigenvalue of the unsigned Laplacian matrix) maximum and minimum are, respectively, K 1 ∨ P n-1 and P 2 n.In [13], the spectrum of the matrix A α for some classes of graphs is considered, in particular, they determine the spectrum of the complete split graph, denoted K s ∨ (n -s)K 1, which is a particular case of k-tree.In [25] the authors prove that the unique outerplanar graph of order n with a maximum value of α-index is K 2 ∨ P n-2.",
    "Furthermore, they prove that, if α ∈ [0.486, 0.5], the unique planar graph of order n with maximum α-indexis K 2 ∨ P n-2.In [17] the authors analyze the nullity (the multiplicity of zero as an eigenvalue of A(G)) of two families of k-trees, the (k +1)-line graphs of k-trees and the free block-connected graphs K 1,k+2, and the simple clique k-trees, which are the k-trees whose (k + 1)-line graphs are trees.",
    "For each pair of integers p ≥ 2 and k ≥ 2, a k-tree is presented such that the nullity of its (k + 1)-row graph is equal to p. Furthermore, the authors establish an upper bound for the nullity of the (k + 1)-row graphs of k-simple clique trees with n vertices."
